article.description: Coley scores 20, Stony Brook tops Binghamton 67-47
article.headline: Coley scores 20, Stony Brook tops Binghamton 67-47
article.linkText: Coley scores 20, Stony Brook tops Binghamton 67-47
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Dave Coley tied a season-high by scoring 20 points while leading Stony Brook to a 67-47 victory over Binghamton Wednesday night. Coley scored 20 points in the Seawolves' last game, a win over Hartford on Jan. 12. Marlon Beck's three-point play with 7:35 left in the first half gave Binghamton (4-13, 1/3 America East) an 18-17 lead. But Carson Puriefoy's jumper sparked a 14-0 run by Stony Brook and his 3-pointer about 5 minutes later capped the spurt. The Seawolves took a 37-23 lead into the break led by at least 13 the rest of the way. Stony Brook (11-6, 3-0) out-rebounded the Bearcats 38-20 while limiting Binghamton to 31.8 percent (14 of 44) shooting. Eric McAlister scored 15 points and Jameel Warney added 13 and nine rebounds. Ahmad Walker had a career-high five steals. Yosef Yacob paced Binghamton with 14 points
